Section.Catchline: Counties that have implemented ch. 83-220; inapplicability of 10-cent tax increase by s. 2, ch. 92-317, Laws of Florida.

SectionBody.Text: The 10-cent tax increase in the documentary stamp tax levied by s. 2, chapter 92-317, does not apply to deeds and other taxable instruments relating to real property located in any county that has implemented the provisions of chapter 83-220, Laws of Florida, as amended by chapters 84-270, 86-152, and 89-252, Laws of Florida. Each such county and each eligible jurisdiction within such county shall not be eligible to participate in programs funded pursuant to s. 201.15(9). However, each such county and each eligible jurisdiction within such county shall be eligible to participate in programs funded pursuant to s. 201.15(10).
